Use ASP.NET Core's **`WebApplicationFactory<T>`** — it hosts your app in-memory with a real HTTP pipeline but no network listener.

### Setup

```bash
dotnet add reference ../src/MyMcpServer.csproj
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Testing
```

### Example test

```csharp
public class McpIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public McpIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _client = factory.CreateClient();
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Initialize_ReturnsCapabilities()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 1,
            method = "initialize",
            @params = new
            {
                protocolVersion = "2025-03-26",
                capabilities = new { },
                clientInfo = new { name = "test-client", version = "1.0" }
            }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        Assert.Equal("2025-03-26",
            body.GetProperty("result")
                .GetProperty("protocolVersion")
                .GetString());
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task ToolsList_ReturnsRegisteredTools()
    {
        var request = new
        {
            jsonrpc = "2.0",
            id = 2,
            method = "tools/list",
            @params = new { }
        };

        var response = await _client.PostAsJsonAsync("/mcp", request);

        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        var body = await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<JsonElement>();
        var tools = body.GetProperty("result").GetProperty("tools");
        Assert.True(tools.GetArrayLength() > 0);
    }
}
```

### Key points

- **`WebApplicationFactory<Program>`** boots the full middleware pipeline in-process — routing, auth, DI, everything.
- **No port binding** — the `HttpClient` talks directly to the in-memory server.
- Make `Program` visible to tests by adding to your server project:
  ```csharp
  // at the bottom of Program.cs (or in a partial class)
  public partial class Program { }
  ```
- Override services (e.g., swap a real DB for an in-memory one) via `factory.WithWebApplicationFactory(b => b.ConfigureServices(...))`.
- For **SSE-based MCP transports**, read the response stream incrementally with `HttpCompletionOption.ResponseHeadersRead` and parse SSE frames from the stream.
